properties.name: 17 Mile Drive
properties.description: Posted by Takewrning 1518 Cypress Drive, Pebble Beach, CAWhen Craig and I went to Monteray Bay, it was the only day of the year that the scenic 17-mile drive was closed to tourists. When we came back, we didn\'t have time to bike it, so drove it and we\'re very happy about it. We were pretty dirty then Craig\'s Debit card didn\'t work in the Pebble Beach gift shop and I almost backed into an SUV when we were leaving.

properties.name: Bob's Lake
properties.description: Posted by Takewrningsharbot lake, ontarioThis is the site of our yearly trip of dads and kids (usually about 20 people) Lots of things have happened, but most recently, my brother and I took out my Dad’s newest prized-possesion, the sail boat. It was the first windy day, and it was REALLY windy. Craig and I couldn’t even get the sail up all the way before it cracked and broke. Someone had to come retrieve us. :-(

properties.name: Full Sail
properties.description: Posted by Takewrning 3300 University Blvd, Winter Park, FL 32792One winter I dated a boy that lived in Orlando. Those were nice weekend visits. I showed up with all my Pittsburgh winter clothes- dark skinny jeans and layers of black. Then we went out- everyone there was in posh pastel clothing. It was a bit awkward and hot.
